Fenway Summer Mortgage to Merge with Ethos Lending
Lefanowicz to Serve as CEO, Carmel as President
















































WASHINGTON, April 8, 2014 /PRNewswire-iReach/ -- Today Fenway Summer LLC, a hybrid advisory and venture investment firm, and Ethos Lending LLC, a residential home lender specializing in agency eligible mortgages, announced the combination of their respective mortgage ventures. The new firm, which will operate under the name Ethos Lending, will build a national mortgage origination business focusing on agency mortgages and prime non-qualified mortgages. 
Fenway Summer LLC has been incubating a non-qualified mortgage company alongside other ventures—including a recently announced credit card venture—for several months. 
"Our mission at Fenway Summer is to build great consumer finance businesses," said Raj Date, Managing Partner of Fenway Summer LLC.  "Our mortgage business, together with Ethos, is a terrific first example – a technology-enabled business that will deliver great products to otherwise underserved customers." 
Ethos Lending anticipates beginning to originate agency mortgages in the 2nd quarter of 2014.  By the end of the year, Ethos plans to be one of the first wholesale originators of non-qualified mortgages.  Ethos will offer affordable and accessible mortgage products that are unavailable in the market today, such as interest-only loans under the current conforming balance threshold of $417,000. 
The company's management team, described in greater detail below, is drawn from Fenway Summer and Ethos Lending LLC.    

Raj Date, founder of Fenway Summer and former Deputy Director of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB), will serve as the Chairman of the Board of Ethos Lending.   
Mark Lefanowicz, who has been serving as CEO of Fenway Summer Mortgage, will serve as CEO of Ethos Lending.  Earlier in his career, Mr. Lefanowicz was CFO of Provident Funding and CEO of E-LOAN. 
Adam Carmel, the founder of Ethos Lending LLC, will serve as President of Ethos Lending.  Prior to founding Ethos, Mr. Carmel was an Executive Vice President at Provident Funding, where he managed servicing and sub-servicing operations.  
Kin Chung will be Chief Credit Officer of Ethos Lending. Mr. Chung joined Fenway Summer after holding senior analytics positions at a variety of leading financial firms, including Fannie Mae and Capital One.  He holds a Ph.D. in Mathematics from Princeton University. 
Erik Stern will be Chief Operating Officer of Ethos Lending.  Mr. Stern has deep experience in mortgage loan underwriting, funding, servicing, and most other operational aspects of the mortgage wholesale business.  Mr. Stern held numerous management positions at Provident Funding. 
Sean Souther will be Chief Information Officer of Ethos Lending.  Mr. Souther has experience in developing unique and cutting-edge technology solutions in the mortgage business.  Mr. Souther has held senior management technology positions at Fidelity National Lending and Lender Processing Services.  
Chris Haspel will lead Capital Markets for Ethos Lending.  Mr. Haspel has deep capital markets experience, including time in leadership positions at the CFPB, Ginnie Mae, Capital One, BlackRock Financial Management, and GE Capital Mortgage. 
Mitch Hochberg will serve as the General Counsel of Ethos Lending.  Prior to joining Fenway Summer, Mr. Hochberg was a Senior Counsel within the CFPB Office of Regulations.  He spent several years at Cadwalader, Wichersham & Taft LLP, where he was responsible for managing several significant litigations relating to mortgage loan underwriting, servicing, and securitization. 
"I had the opportunity to work with Adam earlier in my career; he is a savvy and disciplined operator and a great fit with our team.  We are very excited about our company's unique ability to offer both agency eligible and non-qualifying mortgages to the mortgage broker community," said Mr. Lefanowicz. 
"Ethos has been hard at work building an efficient and scalable mortgage platform," Mr. Carmel said. "Combining our collective core competencies is an exciting opportunity and I am delighted to be partnering with Fenway Summer."
About Fenway Summer:
Fenway Summer LLC is a hybrid advisory and venture investment firm focused on U.S. consumer finance. For more information about Fenway Summer LLC, visit www.fenwaysummer.com. 
Media Contact: Sean O'Mealia, Fenway Summer, 202-864-6225, sean.omealia@fenwaysummer.com 
News distributed by PR Newswire iReach: https://ireach.prnewswire.com 
 SOURCE  Fenway Summer  

Related Links

http://www.fenwaysummer.com












